Shanghai Electric Group Co., a
Chinese maker of electric equipment, sold a 61.35 percent stake
in its unit Shanghai Topsolar Green Energy Co. to Jiangsu King
Sun Power Co. for about 162 million yuan ($24.5 million).  Shanghai Topsolar produces silicon materials, solar cells
and modules, Shanghai Electric said today in a filing to
